Namespaces are used to organize code and prevent naming conflicts.

typescript

Copy code

// Define a namespace
namespace MyNamespace;

// Access a class within the namespace
$obj = new MyClass();

OOP is a programming paradigm that focuses on creating objects with properties and methods. In PHP, classes define objects.

typescript

Copy code

$obj = new MyClass();
class Car {
    public $brand;
    public function startEngine() {
      echo "Engine started.";
    }
}

$myCar = new Car();
$myCar->brand = "Toyota";
$myCar->startEngine();

foreach is used for iterating over arrays or other iterable objects. It simplifies the process of looping through the elements of an array compared to for or while loops. Unlike for or while, foreach doesn't require explicit index management and automatically handles the iteration.

typescript

Copy code

$fruits = ["apple", "banana", "cherry"];
  foreach ($fruits as $fruit) {
    echo $fruit . "<br>";
}

A trait is a reusable code block that can be used by classes in PHP. Traits are similar to classes but cannot be instantiated on their own. They are used to share methods among multiple classes without multiple inheritance conflicts.

typescript

Copy code

trait Loggable {
    public function log($message) {
        echo "Logging: $message";
    }
}class User {
    use Loggable;
}

spl_autoload_register() is used to register a custom function as an autoloader. Autoloaders automatically load class files when they are needed.

typescript

Copy code

function myAutoloader($class) {
    include 'classes/' . $class . '.class.php';
}

spl_autoload_register('myAutoloader');

Magic Methods in PHP are predefined methods that start with double underscores (e.g., __construct()). Some commonly used magic methods include:
__construct() and __destruct(): Constructor and destructor methods.
__get() and __set(): Called when accessing or setting properties.
__toString(): Used to convert an object to a string when echoed.
__call() and __callStatic(): Handles method calls that aren't defined.

typescript

Copy code

class MyClass {
    public function __construct() {
      echo "Object created!";
    }
}

$obj = new MyClass();  // Calls the constructor (__construct)

The "header" function in PHP is used to send HTTP headers to the browser, often used for setting response codes and redirects.

typescript

Copy code

header("Location: https://www.example.com");
exit();

Cookies are small pieces of data stored on the client's browser. They can be used to persist user-specific information across requests.

typescript

Copy code

// Setting a cookie
setcookie("username", "John", time() + 3600, "/");

// Retrieving a cookie
$username = $_COOKIE["username"];

Exception handling in PHP involves the use of try, catch, and optionally, finally blocks. try encloses the code that might throw an exception, catch is used to handle exceptions, and finally is executed regardless of whether an exception was thrown or not.

typescript

Copy code

try {
    // Code that may throw an exception    $result = 10 / 0;
} catch (Exception $e) {
    // Handle the exception    echo "Error: " . $e->getMessage();
} finally {
    // This block will be executed no matter what    echo "Cleanup";
}

json_encode() is used to convert a PHP data structure (arrays or objects) into a JSON-encoded string. It's commonly used for sending data to JavaScript clients.

typescript

Copy code

$data = array("name" => "John", "age" => 30);
$json = json_encode($data);

The Singleton pattern ensures that a class has only one instance and provides a global point of access to that instance.

typescript

Copy code

class Singleton {
    private static $instance;

    private function __construct() {
        // Private constructor to prevent instantiation    }

    public static function getInstance() {
        if (!self::$instance) {
            self::$instance = new self();
        }
        return self::$instance;
    }
}

filter_var() is used for data validation and sanitization. It can validate data against various filters (e.g., email, URL) and sanitize data (e.g., remove HTML tags).

typescript

Copy code

$email = 'example@example.com';if (filter_var($email, FILTER_VALIDATE_EMAIL)) {
    echo 'Valid email address.';
} else {
    echo 'Invalid email address.';
}

A closure, or anonymous function, is a function without a name that can be assigned to variables or passed as arguments to other functions. Closures are often used for tasks like defining callbacks or creating functions on the fly.

typescript

Copy code

$add = function ($a, $b) {
    return $a + $b;
};echo $add(2, 3); // Outputs 5
